		8.2. Catching user input
	.2.1. Using the read built-in command
the syntax of the read command is:
	read [options] NAME1, NAME2, ..., NAMEN
when running it, one line is read from stdin, the 1st word is assigned to NAME1, the second to NAME2 and so on.
the chars on the IFS is used to divide the input into lines

	
